BG.GSR.NFSV.GD.ZS-goodsServicesIncome.def: Trade in services is the sum of service exports and imports divided by the value of GDP, all in current U.S. dollars.
BG.GSR.NFSV.GD.ZS-goodsServicesIncome.name: Trade in services
BG.GSR.NFSV.GD.ZS-goodsServicesIncome.source: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files, and World Bank and OECD GDP estimates.
BG.GSR.NFSV.GD.ZS-goodsServicesIncome.dataset: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files, and World Bank and OECD GDP estimates.

BM.GSR.CMCP.ZS-goodsServicesIncome.def: Communications, computer, information, and other services cover international telecommunications; computer data; news-related service transactions between residents and nonresidents; construction services; royalties and license fees; miscellaneous business, professional, and technical services; personal, cultural, and recreational services; manufacturing services on physical inputs owned by others; and maintenance and repair services and government services not included elsewhere.
BM.GSR.CMCP.ZS-goodsServicesIncome.name: Communications, computer
BM.GSR.CMCP.ZS-goodsServicesIncome.source: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.
BM.GSR.CMCP.ZS-goodsServicesIncome.dataset: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.

BM.GSR.FCTY.CD-goodsServicesIncome.def: Primary income payments refer to employee compensation paid to nonresident workers and investment income (payments on direct investment, portfolio investment, other investments). Data are in current U.S. dollars.
BM.GSR.FCTY.CD-goodsServicesIncome.name: Primary income payments
BM.GSR.FCTY.CD-goodsServicesIncome.source: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.
BM.GSR.FCTY.CD-goodsServicesIncome.dataset: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.

BM.GSR.GNFS.CD-goodsServicesIncome.def: Imports of goods and services comprise all transactions between residents of a country and the rest of the world involving a change of ownership from nonresidents to residents of general merchandise, nonmonetary gold, and services. Data are in current U.S. dollars.
BM.GSR.GNFS.CD-goodsServicesIncome.name: Imports of goods and services
BM.GSR.GNFS.CD-goodsServicesIncome.source: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.
BM.GSR.GNFS.CD-goodsServicesIncome.dataset: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.

BM.GSR.INSF.ZS-goodsServicesIncome.def: Insurance and financial services cover various types of insurance provided to nonresidents by resident insurance enterprises and vice versa, and financial intermediary and auxiliary services (except those of insurance enterprises and pension funds) exchanged between residents and nonresidents.
BM.GSR.INSF.ZS-goodsServicesIncome.name: Insurance and financial services
BM.GSR.INSF.ZS-goodsServicesIncome.source: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.
BM.GSR.INSF.ZS-goodsServicesIncome.dataset: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.

BM.GSR.MRCH.CD-goodsServicesIncome.def: Goods imports refer to all movable goods (including nonmonetary gold) involved in a change of ownership from nonresidents to residents. Data are in current U.S. dollars.
BM.GSR.MRCH.CD-goodsServicesIncome.name: Goods imports
BM.GSR.MRCH.CD-goodsServicesIncome.source: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.
BM.GSR.MRCH.CD-goodsServicesIncome.dataset: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.

BM.GSR.NFSV.CD-goodsServicesIncome.def: Services refer to economic output of intangible commodities that may be produced, transferred, and consumed at the same time. Data are in current U.S. dollars.
BM.GSR.NFSV.CD-goodsServicesIncome.name: Service imports
BM.GSR.NFSV.CD-goodsServicesIncome.source: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.
BM.GSR.NFSV.CD-goodsServicesIncome.dataset: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.

BM.GSR.ROYL.CD-goodsServicesIncome.def: Charges for the use of intellectual property are payments and receipts between residents and nonresidents for the authorized use of proprietary rights (such as patents, trademarks, copyrights, industrial processes and designs including trade secrets, and franchises) and for the use, through licensing agreements, of produced originals or prototypes (such as copyrights on books and manuscripts, computer software, cinematographic works, and sound recordings) and related rights (such as for live performances and television, cable, or satellite broadcast). Data are in current U.S. dollars.
BM.GSR.ROYL.CD-goodsServicesIncome.name: Charges for the use of intellectual property
BM.GSR.ROYL.CD-goodsServicesIncome.source: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.
BM.GSR.ROYL.CD-goodsServicesIncome.dataset: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.

BM.GSR.TOTL.CD-goodsServicesIncome.def: Imports of goods, services and primary income is the sum of goods imports, service imports and primary income payments. Data are in current U.S. dollars.
BM.GSR.TOTL.CD-goodsServicesIncome.name: Imports of goods, services and primary income
BM.GSR.TOTL.CD-goodsServicesIncome.source: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.
BM.GSR.TOTL.CD-goodsServicesIncome.dataset: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.

BM.GSR.TRAN.ZS-goodsServicesIncome.def: Transport covers all transport services (sea, air, land, internal waterway, pipeline, space and electricity transmission) performed by residents of one economy for those of another and involving the carriage of passengers, the movement of goods (freight), rental of carriers with crew, and related support and auxiliary services. Also included are postal and courier services. Excluded are freight insurance (included in insurance services); goods procured in ports by nonresident carriers (included in goods); maintenance and repairs on transport equipment (included in maintenance and repair services n.i.e.); and repairs of railway facilities, harbors, and airfield facilities (included in construction).
BM.GSR.TRAN.ZS-goodsServicesIncome.name: Transport services
BM.GSR.TRAN.ZS-goodsServicesIncome.source: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.
BM.GSR.TRAN.ZS-goodsServicesIncome.dataset: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.

BM.GSR.TRVL.ZS-goodsServicesIncome.def: Travel covers goods and services acquired from an economy by travelers for their own use during visits of less than one year in that economy for either business or personal purposes. Travel includes local transport (i.e., transport within the economy being visited and provided by a resident of that economy), but excludes international transport (which is included in passenger transport. Travel also excludes goods for resale, which are included in general merchandise.
BM.GSR.TRVL.ZS-goodsServicesIncome.name: Travel services
BM.GSR.TRVL.ZS-goodsServicesIncome.source: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.
BM.GSR.TRVL.ZS-goodsServicesIncome.dataset: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.

BN.GSR.FCTY.CD-goodsServicesIncome.name: Net primary income

BN.GSR.FCTY.CD-goodsServicesIncome.dataset: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.
